oc:kn_00b69f5d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During the first two weeks of a new campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Not giving algorithms enough learning time (7+ days with 50+ conversions) before making changes is a top cause of poor campaign performance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature optimization based on noisy early data disrupts the learning phase and resets the algorithm, creating a cycle of poor performance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1d937352 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During weekly campaign review" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Look for: CPM consistent with platform benchmarks, CTR above platform averages, frequency below fatigue thresholds (3x/week for warm audiences), and conversion rate stable or improving." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These leading indicators detect problems before they blow through budget, and confirm when campaigns are healthy." .

oc:kn_41a244ca a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Immediately before launching any campaign on any platform" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before launching: verify conversion tracking with a real test conversion, landing page loads under 3 seconds, page is mobile-friendly, UTMs are working, budget is correct, and targeting matches intended audience." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These six checks catch the most common launch-killer issues that waste budget in the first hours of a campaign." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_41e5b9ba a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When first launching or expanding paid advertising" ;
    oc:directiveContent "During the testing phase (first 2-4 weeks), allocate 70% of budget to proven/safe campaigns and 30% to testing new audiences and creative." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This balances risk reduction with learning, ensuring you don't burn budget on unproven combinations while still gathering data." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_508270dd a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring campaigns and allocating budget" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid fragmenting budget across too many campaigns — this starves each campaign of data and prevents algorithmic learning." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ad platform algorithms need sufficient conversion data per campaign to optimize delivery. Spread too thin, nothing learns." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_50a13b10 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing campaign performance and reporting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Platform attribution numbers are inflated — always compare platform-reported CPA against GA4 data and calculate blended CAC." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Platforms take credit for conversions they didn't solely cause, leading to overstated performance and poor budget decisions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_72f613a3 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up audience targeting for any campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not exclude existing customers and recent converters from prospecting campaigns — showing ads to people who already bought wastes spend." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Excluding converters prevents burning budget on people who already took the desired action, improving true incremental CPA." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8be8dfab a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating video ad creative for any platform" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The first 3 seconds of video ads determine success — use a pattern interrupt, bold question, or unexpected statement as the hook." ;
    oc:hasRationale "85% of viewers watch without sound and attention spans are minimal; the hook must arrest scrolling immediately." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a77c1097 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating lookalike audiences on Meta or other platforms" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Base lookalike audiences on best customers by LTV, not all customers — purchasers outperform leads, which outperform all visitors as a source." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The quality of the seed audience directly determines lookalike quality. Using low-value customers teaches the algorithm to find more low-value users." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_c45a6ab2 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before launching any campaign on any platform" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never launch campaigns without conversion tracking tested with a real conversion — you cannot optimize what you cannot measure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without conversion tracking, you're spending blind with no way to determine ROAS or validate that spend drives real outcomes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_dfaff4ab a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When campaigns are running but cost-per-acquisition exceeds targets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If CPA is too high: (1) check the landing page for post-click issues, (2) tighten audience targeting, (3) test new creative angles, (4) improve relevance/quality score, (5) adjust bid strategy." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic diagnosis from post-click through pre-click ensures you find the actual bottleneck rather than guessing." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ead19571 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During the scaling phase of a successful campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Increase budgets by only 20-30% at a time and wait 3-5 days between increases to avoid disrupting the algorithm learning phase." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Large budget changes reset the platform's learning phase, causing volatile performance and wasted spend while the algorithm re-calibrates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

